description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are looking forPsychiatric Nurse / social workerto join us!!!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Are you an enthusiastic, motivated and hard-working individual? Are you looking for a new challenge and an opportunity to be involved in a dynamic, forward-thinking, and exciting team?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the answers are yes, then we would love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;** We are offering £2,500 Golden Hello Payment to external candidates from outside of Hampshire and Isle of Wight! **&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Relocation package is also available!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Southern Health NHS is one of the largest mental health trusts in England, and we are constantly expanding our teams!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Right now, our Community Mental Health Team (CMHT) at the Bridge Centre in Basingstoke is looking for nurses and social workers to join them!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CMHT is a lively, dynamic and busy multi-disciplinary team which provides care coordination and recovery focused care for individuals with complex and challenging mental health needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a practitioner to join our dynamic and recovery focused team. This would be a great developmental opportunity for a band 5 looking to broaden their experience within mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will play an important role in delivering excellent care for our service users, and working as part of the team to provide the right support and assistance to our service users in their recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Leading and contributing in the process of planning and coordinating service user care and undertaking interventions in line with agreed care plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Delivering higher level intensity community interventions as part of the integrated Shared Care model&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Formulating care plans in line with assessed need&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Working in a manner which is helpful to the service user and the referrer, based on principles of recovery, personalisation and choice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Working with individuals in the least restrictive manner possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Working in a service which may include some weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· You will have previous experience in the effective and positive management of people with mental health needs and will be able to evidence effective team working and leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ability to drive and use of a car for work purpose is essential in this role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Trust offers continuous development for all of our staff, as well as regular supervision and annual appraisal, to ensure you achieve your personal goals and assist you in personal and professional development. Regular support from your line manager is also provided to ensure you have the opportunity to develop your skills further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The benefits to working at the Bridge Centre:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Buying additional annual leave&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Charitable giving via payroll&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· NHS Discounts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Regular team social events&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Yearly appraisals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Development days&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Individual training opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Team bonding away days&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Close relations with local agencies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information on this role, please contact Ian Whaites - Nursing Team Leader on01256 316300&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
